text: Drypetes hoaensis is an Asian tree species in the family Putranjivaceae. The recorded occurrence of this species is from Yunnan, Thailand and Vietnam (where it may be called sang trắng Biên Hòa or táo vòng Biên Hòa). == References == == External links== Category: Flora of Indo-China Category: Trees of Vietnam hoaensis
title: Drypetes hoaensis
